This article explains how to install and configure command line tools for use with [[ImageJ]] development.

== Install and configure command line tools ==

=== Setting up command line tools on Windows ===
* Download and install the [http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/index.html Java 6 JDK], [http://msysgit.github.com/ Git for Windows] and [http://maven.apache.org/download.html Maven].
* Add the <code>bin</code> directory for each to your [http://op111.net/82/ PATH environment variable].

=== Setting up command line tools on Mac OS X ===
Using [http://brew.sh/ Homebrew]:
<source lang="bash">
brew install git maven bash-completion
</source>

=== Setting up command line tools on Ubuntu ===
<source lang="bash">
sudo apt-get install default-jdk git maven
</source>

== Download the source ==
<source lang="bash">
git clone git://github.com/imagej/imagej
</source>
See the [[Source Code]] page for further details.

== Build the source ==
<source lang="bash">
cd imagej
mvn
</source>

== Launch the program ==
<source lang="bash">
mvn -Pexec
</source>

=== Launching alternative user interfaces ===
<source lang="bash">
mvn -Dimagej.ui=swing -Pexec
mvn -Dimagej.ui=swing-mdi -Pexec
mvn -Dimagej.ui=awt -Pexec
mvn -Dimagej.ui=pivot -Pexec
mvn -Dimagej.ui=swt -Pexec
</source>
